x4freetext: .THREE MOLYBDENUM SAMPLES WERE USED - 1.0 G NATURAL
MO, 300 MILLI-G ENRICHED MO-98 AND 300 MILLI-G
ENRICHED MO-100. EACH SAMPLE WAS PACKED IN A THIN
POLYTHENE BAG AND SURROUNDED BY A 99.99 PER CENT
PURE AL MONITOR FOIL, AND THEN PACKED IN A
.THE ISOTOPIC COMPOSITION IN ATOMS PER CENT  WAS -
COAXIAL 55 CM3 GE(LI) DETECTOR, WITH FWHM
50 CM FROM THE TRITIUM TARGET AT AN ANGLE
OF 179 DEGREES TO THE BEAM, USED TO MONITOR
THE NEUTRON FLUX BY COUNTING ALPHA PARTICLES
A.P.T. JAPAN CODE CHANGED TO JPN
.SELF ABSORPTION OF GAMMA RAYS IN THE SAMPLE.
IN DETECTOR EFFICIENCIES ( LESS THAN 5 PER
CENT ) MONITOR CROSS SECTIONS AND COUNTING
.THE SAMPLES WERE WEIGHED TO AN ACCURACY OF 0.03 PER
CENT OR BETTER. THIS ERROR IS NEGLIGIBLE COMPARED TO
.THE QUOTED ERROR DOES NOT INCLUDE CONTRIBUTIONS FROM
UNCERTAINTIES IN THE HALF LIVES OR THE GAMMA
